  "prompt": "Who is the best doctor for cardiology in India?",
  "response": "It's challenging to single out one \"best\" doctor for cardiology in India, as there are many highly skilled and experienced cardiologists across the country. However, here are a few renowned cardiologists who are widely recognized for their expertise and contributions to the field:\n\n1. **Dr. Ashok Seth**  \n   - Chairman of Fortis Escorts Heart Institute, New Delhi.  \n   - One of India's most respected cardiologists, known for his pioneering work in interventional cardiology.  \n\n2. **Dr. Devi Prasad Shetty**  \n   - Founder and Chairman of Narayana Health, Bengaluru.  \n   - Renowned for making cardiac care affordable and accessible.  \n\n3. **Dr. Naresh Trehan**  \n   - Chairman and Managing Director of Medanta - The Medicity, Gurgaon.  \n   - A leading cardiothoracic surgeon with extensive experience in complex cardiac procedures.  \n\n4. **Dr. K.K. Talwar**  \n   - Former Director of Post Graduate Institute of Medical Education and Research (PGIMER), Chandigarh.  \n   - A distinguished cardiologist with expertise in heart failure and interventional cardiology.  \n\n5. **Dr. Upendra Kaul**  \n   - Executive Director and Dean at Fortis Escorts Heart Institute, New Delhi.  \n   - Known for his contributions to interventional cardiology and research.  \n\n6. **Dr. Ramakanta Panda**  \n   - Chief of Asian Heart Institute, Mumbai.  \n   - One of the leading cardiac surgeons in India, specializing in complex heart surgeries.  \n\nWhen choosing a cardiologist, it's essential to consider factors such as their expertise, experience, patient reviews, and the hospital's facilities. Consulting with a cardiologist who best suits your specific needs and condition is crucial. Always consult multiple professionals and seek referrals if needed.",
